\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 
Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy on me.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Troparia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par I have willfully incurred the guilt of Cain's murder, since by invigorating my flesh I am the murderer of my soul's awareness, and have warred against it by my evil deeds. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Genesis 4:8)}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par I have not resembled Abel's righteousness, O Jesus. I have never offered Thee acceptable gifts, nor divine actions, nor a pure sacrifice, nor an unblemished life. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Genesis 4:4)}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par Like Cain, we too, O wretched soul, have likewise offered to the Creator of all foul deeds, defective sacrifice and a useless life. Therefore we too are condemned. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 
(Genesis 4:5; Hebrews 11:4) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par In molding my clay into life, O Potter, Thou didst put in me flesh and bones, breath and vitality. But, O my Creator, my Redeemer and Judge, accept me who repent. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 
(Genesis 2:7; Jeremiah 18:1-10; Rom. 9:21) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par I confess to Thee, O Savior, the sins I have committed, and the wounds of my body and soul which murderous thoughts like robbers within have inflicted upon me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Luke 10:30) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par I have sinned, O Savior, yet I know that Thou art the Lover of men. Thou strikest compassionately and pitiest warmly. Thou seest me weeping and runnest towards me as the Father recalling the Prodigal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Luke 15:20) 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid8548906 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit: 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 To The Trinity:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  Superessential Trinity, adored in
 Unity, take from me the heavy yoke of sin, and in Thy compassion grant me tears of compunction. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\insrsid8548906 Now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Theotokion:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
 Mother of God, hope and intercessor of those who sing of thee, take from me the heavy yoke of sin, and as thou art our pure Lady, accept me who repent. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\keep\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid8548906 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect
