Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy on me. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Troparia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par When the Ark was being carried on a wagon, and when one of the oxen slipped, Uzzah only touched it and experienced the wrath of God. But avoid, my soul, his presumption and truly reverence divine things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (II Kings 6:6) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par You have heard of Absalom, how he rose against nature. You know his accursed deeds and how he insulted the bed of his father David. But you have imitated his passionate and pleasure-loving cravings. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (II Kings 15; 16:21)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par You have enslaved your free dignity to your body, my soul, for you have found in satan another Ahitophel and have consented to his counsels. But Christ Himself scattered them, that you may at all events be saved. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (II Kings 16:20) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par Wonderful Solomon, who was full of the grace of wisdom, at one time did evil in God's sight and fell away from Him. And you, my soul, have resembled him by your accursed life. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 
(III Kings 11; Ecclus. 47:12-20) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par Carried away by the pleasure of his passions, he defiled himself. Alas, the lover of wisdom is a lover of loose women and estranged from God! And you, my soul, have in mind imitated him by your shameful pleasures. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (III Kings 3:12; 11:4-12) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par You, my soul, have rivaled Rehoboam who would not listen to his father's advisors, and that vicious slave Jeroboam the apostate of old. But shun such mimicry and cry to God: I have sinned, have compassion on me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (III Kings 12:13-20) 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 To The Trinity:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  O Trinity simple and undivided, of one essence and one nature, Lights and Light, three Holies and one Holy
, God the Trinity is hymned. But sing, my soul, and glorify the Life and Lives, the God of all. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Theotokion:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  We sing of thee, we bless thee, we worship thee, O Mother of God, for thou gavest birth to one of t
he inseparable Trinity, the one Son and God, and to us on earth thou hast opened the heavenly realms. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\keep\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid8548906 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect
