\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Troparia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par Having emulated Uzziah, my soul, you have his leprosy in you doubled. For you think disgusting thoughts and do outrageous things. Let go of what you are holding and run to repentance. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 
(IV Kings 15:5; II Chronicles 26:19)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par Have you heard, my soul, of the Ninevites, who repented before God in sackcloth and ashes? You have not imitated them, but appear to be more crooked than all who have sinned before and after the law. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Jonah 3:5) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par You have heard of Jeremiah in the mud pit, my soul, how he cried out with lamentations against the City of Zion, and was seeking tears. Imitate his life of lamentation and you will be saved. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Jeremiah 38:6)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par Jonah fled to Tarshish, foreseeing the conversion of the Ninevites; for, being a Prophet, he was aware of God's compassion, and was anxious that his prophecy should not prove false. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 
(Jonah 1:3) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par You have heard, my soul, of Daniel in the lion's den. and how he shut the beasts' mouths. You know how the Children who were with Azariah extinguished the flames of the burning furnace by faith. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Dan. 6:16-22; 3:23)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par I have reviewed all the people of the Old Testament as examples for you, my soul. Imitate the God-loving deeds of the righteous and shun the sins of the wicked. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 To The Trinity:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
 Eternal Father, co-eternal Son, gracious Comforter, Spirit of Truth; Father of the Divine Word, Word of the Eternal Father, living and creative Spirit, Trinity Unity, have mercy on us. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Theotokion:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
 As from scarlet silk, O spotless Virgin, within thy womb the spiritual purple was woven, the flesh Of Emmanuel. Therefore we honor thee as in truth Mother of God. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\keep\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid8548906 \sect }\sectd \ltrsect
