\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Eirmos:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Ineffable is the childbe
aring of a seedless conception, unsullied the pregnancy of a Virgin Mother, for the birth of God renews natures. So in all generations we magnify thee in orthodox fashion as the Mother and Bride of God. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 
Have mercy on me, O God, have mercy on me. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Troparia:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par Christ was tempted, the devil was tempting Him, showing Him stones to be turned into bread; and he led Him up a mountain to see all the kingdoms of the world in a flash. Dread, my soul, the scene; watch and pray at every hour to God. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Matthew 4:3-9; 26:41) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par The desert-loving dove, the lamp of Christ, the Voice crying in the wilderness sounded, preaching repentance; while Herod sinned with Herodias. See, my soul, that you are not caught in the toils of sin, but embrace repentance. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Mark 1:3; Matthew 14:3) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par The Forerunner of grace dwelt in the desert and all Judea and Samaria ran to hear him; and they confessed their sins, and eagerly received baptism. But you, my soul, have not imitated them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Matthew 3:5-6) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par Marriage is honourable and the bed undefiled, for Christ earlier blessed both, eating in His flesh at the marriage in Cana and changing water into wine, and showing His first miracle so that you, my soul, might be changed. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 
\ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Hebrews 13:4; John 2:1-11) }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par 
\par Christ braced the paralytic and he carried his bed; He raised up the dead young man, the son of the widow, and the Centurion's servant; and by revealing Himself to the Samaritan woman, He traced in advance for you, my soul, how to worship in spirit. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Matthew 9:2-7; Luke 7:14; Matthew 8:6-13; John 4:26; Josh. 4:24)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par The Lord healed the woman with hemorrhage by the touch of His hem, cleansed lepers, gave sight to the blind, and cured cripples; the deaf and the dumb and the woman bent earthward he healed with His word, that you, wretched soul, might be saved. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs16 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs16\insrsid8548906 (Matthew 9:20-22; 10:8; 11:5; Luke 13:11-13) 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Glory to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Spirit:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 To The Trinity:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  Let us glorify the Father, exalt the Son, and faithfully worship the Divine Spirit, inseparable Trinity, U
nity in essence, as the Light and Lights, the Life and Lives, giving life and light to the ends of the earth. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Now and ever, and to the ages of ages. Amen. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Theotokion:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  Protect thy city, spotless Mother of God, for in thee it faithfully reigns, and in th
ee is made strong, and through thee it conquers and routs every trial and temptation, and spoils its foes and rules its subjects. 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 Refrain:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs36 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs21\f1\fs36\cf15\cgrid0\insrsid8548906 Holy father Andrew, pray for us.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 To St. Andrew of Crete:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  Venerable Andrew, thrice-blessed father, shepherd of Cre
te, cease not to pray to God for those who sing of thee, that He may deliver from anger, oppression, corruption and our countless sins, all of us who faithfully honor thy memory . 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs18\i\f1\cf6\insrsid8548906 And again the Eirmos:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs17\f1\fs32\insrsid8548906  
\par 
